<li><a href="http://www.tedpavlic.com/teaching/osu/ece209/support/circuits_sys_review.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.tedpavlic.com/teaching/osu/ece209/support/circuits_sys_review.pdf" rel="nofollow">ECE 209: Review of Circuits as LTI Systems</a> — Short primer on the mathematical analysis of (electrical) LTI systems.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.tedpavlic.com/teaching/osu/ece209/lab3_opamp_FO/lab3_opamp_FO_phase_shift.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.tedpavlic.com/teaching/osu/ece209/lab3_opamp_FO/lab3_opamp_FO_phase_shift.pdf" rel="nofollow">ECE 209: Sources of Phase Shift</a> — Gives an intuitive explanation of the source of phase shift in a low-pass filter. Also verifies simple passive LPF <a href="/wiki/Transfer_function" title="Transfer function">transfer function</a> by means of trigonometric identity.</li>
</ul>


